MBOMBELA &#8211; The local department&#8217;s officials are picketing before work and during their lunch hour ahead of the strike that will start as of next week.The employees are protesting against having a six-day work week, stating that they either want Saturdays off, or to be paid for overtime.&#8220;We want a normal forty-hour week like everybody else, or they have to pay us extra, but we cannot go on like this,&#8221; one official said.Due to the picketing only happening before work and during the lunch hour (13:00-13:30), the office will remain open, and business can continue throughout the day.An official strike had been arranged to start on Monday.